I think Donald Trump is a ruthless liar about his sexual misconduct scandal.  Here's why. He wasn't shy about bragging about his awful behaviours towards women in the Access Hollywood tape. However, he claimed that he never put his lewd words in the tape into actions.   Secondly,  I was based on what I had heard in a Toronto university campus near Dundas subway station in Canada in 2005.  One evening before the Christmas break in  2005, I overheard a Journalism Professor was having a conversation with another person about his former student's terrifying experience while interviewing a famous businessman in US.  He claimed that the businessman as "one of the most powerful men in the country like Donald Trump".  The professor mentioned that he was concerned that if his student exposes the incident, there may be the risk of retaliation by the perpetrator. I still remember there were numerous details in the conversations which were the same as what was published and broadcasted on the news in 2016.  I do not know them personally and I am not affilated to the same faculty program.I believe that many women who came forward against the current US President are telling the truth.  You will always have our support.  In my daily prayers, I pray that justice will find its way against all odds to punish all the wrongdoers.  May God gives strength and hope to all who are constantly facing belittlement and intimidation for any justifiable cause.  Sometimes the unfair comments against the victims and their supporters are really getting out of hands.I have heard a famous saying that goes like "Life is about what you achieve and what you get away with."  Nonetheless, it is impossible to get away every time without any consequence.  What goes around comes around is the philosophy of many people and hopefully it will apply in the tough reality soon. To whoever that will apply, you can get tremendous power, but you cannot get tremendous respect.
